ZCZC OE77
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 252300 UTC
A SLOW MOV HIGH PRESSURE SYSTEM 1040 CENTRED OVER SCOTLAND GRADUALLY
INTENSIFIES AND BECOMES 1043 BY THE AFTERNOON ON TUESDAY. THIS HIGH THEN
DRIFTS NWWARDS AND DECLINES TO 1030 BY 1800 UTC ON THURSDAY. THROUGHOUT THE
FCST PERIOD THE HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND A RIDGE SWARDS OVER THE UK. ON
MONDAY EVENING WIDESPREAD STRG WINDS ARE EXP ACROSS THE W OF SHANNON ROCKALL
AND BAILEY. THESE WINDS WILL SOON DRIFT WWARDS DEPARTING THE REGION DURING
THE SMALL HOURS OF TUESDAY. ON TUESDAY MORNING ISOL STRG WINDS ARE POSS
ACROSS THE S E ICELAND AREA AS THE HIGH DRIFTS NWWARDS. OVERNIGHT GOING INTO
WEDNESDAY THE WINDS ACROSS S E ICELAND WILL BEGIN TO EASE. BEYOND THIS
THERE ARE NO STRG WINDS OR GALES EXP DURING THE FCST PERIOD ACROSS THE PORTPATRICK
AREA DUE TO THE HIGH PRESSURE SYSTEM CENTRED OVER SCOTLAND
